			<ns0:name>chris.ro...@gmail.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/109476958443797771315/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Note: The PPB_Context3DTrusted_* RPC server interfaces don't appear to have client side equivalent calls. These server side dispatchers are theoretically still reachable by an untrusted NEXE via SRPC.

The CreateTransferBuffer function on line 213 of browser_graphics_3d.cc takes a size parameter provided by an untrusted NEXE module. This size parameter is passed to the CommandBufferService::CreateTransferBuffer() where it is passed to CreateAnonymous and CreateNamed functions. On Win32 platforms if MAX_UINT is provided for size it will overflow on line 92 of shared_memory_win.cc in SharedMemory::CreateNamed 

...
 uint32 rounded_size = (size + 0xffff) &amp;amp; ~0xffff; 
